How to Execute ExtendScript in Premiere Pro <L=l#1></L><I=1>
Executing scripts from within CEP panels is the recommended approach.

With additional configuration work, it's also possible to pass scripts to Premiere Pro on a command line.
This is not recommended, as behavior varies across platforms, and preliminary configuration is necessary
before such execution is enabled.

Use VSCode with Adobe's extension for development and debugging; for deployed workflows, stick with
panels whenever possible.

