Time object <L=p#1></L><I=1>
 myTime = new Time() 

Description <L=p#2></L><I=2>
An object representing a time. Internally, the time is computed in  ticks  ; there are 254016000000 ticks
per second. That time can be accessed in different representations, including as a timecode string.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Attributes <L=p#3></L><I=3>
Time.seconds <L=p#4></L><I=4>
